<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 29 at 7:31PM MDT until June 29 at 8:00PM MDT by NWS Aberdeen</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 900 PM CDT
FOR CENTRAL CLARK AND SOUTHEASTERN SPINK COUNTIES...
At 830 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Clark Colony,
or 13 miles west of Clark, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Fordham Colony, Raymond, Clark and Hillcrest Colony.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
